narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: The course offered us insights into contemporary Latin American politics and inequality in the region, ranging from subjects of corruption, partisanship, to political violence.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The course was extremely well facilitated to encourage student learning, our discussions were very engaging and the material was very interesting.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: If you are looking for a medium-work introduction to politics and inequality in Latin America then this course is solid. Professor de la O is smart and many of the readings were quite interesting. That being said, much of the class material is pretty general and many of the class discussions were a little sleepy.
Yes, I would recommend this course to any student with an interest in Latin American politics.
